section.section:
"Charter" includes:
A charter granted by special act of the General Assembly;
Articles or certificate of incorporation;
Amended articles or certificate of incorporation;
Articles of restatement, if approved as described in § 2-609 of this article;
Articles of amendment and restatement; and
Articles or agreements of consolidation.

text.section:
"Successor" means:
A new corporation formed by consolidation;
A corporation or other entity surviving a merger;
A corporation acquiring stock in a share exchange; or
A vendee, lessee, or other transferee in a transfer of assets.
